Tambunting Pawnshop is the oldest pawnshop in the Philippines, operating since 1906. The essence of business in Tambunting Pawnshop is lending money and accepting jewelry or storage (gadgets and appliances), and even mortgages of real estate and pledges of stocks as collateral. Loans are generally for a maximum period of six months, after which the collateral will be sold at auction or through their other jewelry outlets. Tambunting Pawnshop reached its centennial in 2006 and is currently celebrating its 110th anniversary this year.
